modules.description: This module organizes and runs hierarchical benchmarks using tree structures, where nodes represent named benchmarks or subtrees. It supports operations to build, merge, prefix, and filter benchmark trees, and allows benchmark execution with latency or throughput metrics. Concrete use cases include timing functions at various input sizes, grouping related benchmarks under named paths, and selectively running subsets of benchmarks based on command-line arguments.

This module measures execution times of functions using latency or throughput tests, returning detailed timing metrics like wallclock, CPU, and garbage collection statistics. It works with lists of functions and inputs, producing structured benchmark results that can be tabulated or compared. Concrete use cases include timing cryptographic operations, sorting algorithms, or parsing functions under varying input sizes or configurations.
